Teachers have been warned against working as party agents during the nominations, which begin today. TSC officer in-charge of public primary schools Agatha Murungi said it is unlawful for a serving teacher to engage in politics.She addressed the press on Monday at Farm View resort in Busia town after the official opening of Western region primary school heads' workshop&ldquo;So I want to caution teachers against being recruited as political party agents during or after the party nominations scheduled for Thursday as stern action will be taken against those involved in accordance with the law,&rdquo; she said.She said the TSC has sent notice letters to all primary school head teachers banning tuition during the April holiday.&ldquo;... respective county directors of education should ensure the directive is implemented to the letter,&rdquo; Murungi said.